Citation.sTitle: Studying the Liquid-Liquid Equilibrium of Systems Water +2-Hydroxyethylammonium Propanoate or 2-Hydroxyethylammonium Butanoate or 2-Hydroxyethylammonium Pentanoate +1-Pentanol at 293.15, 313.15, and 333.15 K: Experimental Determination and Thermodynamic Modeling
Citation.sAbstract: Data on the liquid-liquid equilibrium (LLE) for the systems water + [2 HEA][Pr], [2 HEA][Bu] and [2 HEA][Pe] + 1-pentanol were determined at 293.15, 313.15, and 333.15 K and atmospheric pressure. Phase diagrams of the ternary systems were determined using the turbidimetric titration method and the tie-lines were quantified using the gravimetric method. Othmer-Tobias correlation confirms the quality of the experimental LLE data (R2 greater than 0.95). The NRTL (nonrandom two-liquid) and UNIQUAC (universal quasichemical) models were used to predict LLE data, with satisfactory results of root-mean-square deviations (RMSD) of each model at 1.55 and 1.90%, respectively.
